This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of "Computation and Language" (cs.CL) as it deals with natural language processing and specifically focuses on measuring social biases in sentence encoders. It could also belong to "Machine Learning" (cs.LG) as it tests several state-of-the-art methods for bias. Additionally, it could be categorized under "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI) as it deals with the development of intelligent systems that can understand and process human language. "Computers and Society" (cs.CY) is also a possible sub-category as the paper examines biases related to social constructs. Finally, "Social and Information Networks" (cs.SI) is another possible sub-category as the paper deals with biases in social networks and their impact on language processing.
